h this intervention. However, for each of the other two interventions, there was increased support for a positive effect (73&#x000a0;% probability) than there was prior to undertaking the study (50&#x000a0;% probability).<table-wrap id="Tab2"><label>Table 2</label><caption><p>Physical activity at follow-up by arm and comparisons between each VBI and control</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><thead><tr><th/><th>Motivational VBI Mean (95&#x000a0;% CI)</th><th>Pedometer VBI Mean (95&#x000a0;% CI)</th><th>Combined VBI Mean 95&#x000a0;% (CI)</th><th>Control Mean (95&#x000a0;% CI)</th><th>Motivational VBI Relative to Control: Comparison of means (95&#x000a0;% CI) <sup>a</sup>
